caption: Orange chicken was hard and had no taste and chicken fried rice had a funny taste. Would give a 0 out of 5 if i could.

We ordered from here for the first time Today and we were not impressed. The egg rolls were way overcooked and were like rubber.  I had General Tsos chicken which was extremely dry. I couldn’t get a steak knife through the majority of the pieces of chicken. The only decent thing was the fried rice. We will not order from here again.

Prices are fairly cheap, but that compensates for the bad taste of their dishes. Kung Pao Chicken has a bad after taste that will leave you questioning if you should take another bite. The flavor of the chicken was by far the worst I’ve tried. Egg rolls were actually quite nice, crispy outer layer with a delicious interior. Seshwan Vegeterian was decent , the vegetables were coming straight out the refrigerator onto the pan. I will not be back , and I would not recommend.
The best Chinese food I’ve ever had the staff is so polite and their prices are great I highly recommend will never go anywhere else

Absolutely magnificent Chinese cuisine...Best in Chicago! This family-owned restaurant is small in size, but the food packs a wallop in flavor!  The orange chicken is tender, and the orange sauce which graces each sumptuous morsel is fragrant with luscious orange and the perfect blend of heat and sweetness. The heat can easily be adjusted to your taste.  I have tried almost every item on the menu and have never, ever been disappointed.  The husband and wife duo who own and operate Excelsior are always friendly and courteous, and the restaurant itself is clean and comfortable.  Please, please go to Excelsior Garden!  Once tried, you will make this restaurant one of your favorites!

1st time customer and will definitely order again. Fair prices, very good very fresh food. The shrimp was cooked perfect and was super fresh. Mongolian beef was one of the best I've had in years as well. Well done excelsior garden.
Delicious food. I have never been disappointed here
The best tasting chinese food on area
Authentic Chinese food at very reasonable price
Absolutely LOVE this place! Delicious food, good prices, and a welcoming staff :)

I walked past this place for YEARS commuting to work and I'm so upset because I was so missing out! Family run establishment with a HUGE menu with tons of options (black pepper chicken, salt n pepper shrimp, beef n broccoli) that all taste so fresh and the portions make it so you can eat for two days!

The food is always hot, fresh, and absolutely delicious. Portions are generous, especially for the price! The staff is always friendly too, even as they’re busy with a big order. Excelsior Garden is a neighborhood gem!

My go-to for Chinese on this side of Chicago. The food is always good, and their portions are generous--so much so, I usually have plenty leftover for a meal the next day (and it's still delicious reheated).
My favorite is the Schezwan chicken low mein. Converted another from beef and broccoli. Good amount of food for the price, very tasty. The people that own/work there are very friendly.
The best coconut 🥥 smoothie on the planet!

Always great to be able to order from here. We used to live close, but moved to nw burbs. Still order and pick up from here... It's well worth it!

Let's be realistic, Chinese take out is a dime a dozen. But when I find a dish that one makes better than others I stick with it. They make an awesome Cantonese chow mein, haven't been able to find a better one!! Mongolian beef & eggrolls are pretty good. I go to other places when I want great rice & other dishes🤷‍♀️.

We've been coming here for years. Even after we moved we still make the trip back because no other Chinese takeout we've tried has even come close. Their food is so fresh and delicious!! We get a huge order everytime so we have lots of leftovers. Love you guys!

Ordered from here at least once a week as it is on the direct path home. The food is mediocre so unless you are getting a lunch special don't bother.  Oh, and if you are hoping for a warm greeting...don't. The woman that works there is always crabby. Also if they screw up your order they expect you to drive it back and they will not replace it for free. There are so many other places in a few blocks of this place that the little extra travel is worth it.

Delivery took over 1-1/2 hours! The previous order was almost 2 hours! Unacceptable! Yes, food tastes pretty good. I love it, but if my family starves to death by the time it gets here, then why should I give them my business. I mean, when I let them know about this, all I heard was excuses. I told them, make a change then.  Hire more help or lose customers, your choice. I don't write many reviews, but in this case I had too. They need to make a change.
